cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual tracking and proposes a method to enhance the temporal appearance model. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses Discriminative Correlation Filters (DCF) which is a machine learning-based tracking method. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a method to improve the performance of a tracking algorithm using low-rank constraints and a global descriptor. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with tracking objects in videos, which is a multimedia application. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes a method to improve the robustness of a tracking algorithm, which could be useful in robotics applications.
